\section{Conclusions}
It is the slope corner diffracted field that eliminates the discontinuities of the slope diffracted field at the edge diffraction shadow boundaries (EDSB), thus accounting the termination of the edge. The discontinuities at the EDSB is now known, and used to determine the finite-edge slope diffracted field. Incorporation of correction due to finite edge effect into the UTD fields, the result is in good agreement with the measured results even in the $120^\circ-174^\circ$ region. Agreement with Measurement at near $175^\circ$, which is not predicted by the earlier methods, is now predicted.


