Empirical formula gives the rough estimations of AF of an open-ended rectangular waveguide. But the FDTD computed AF is very accurate with respect to the measurements. The variation of AF with respect to the frequency is less for a good EMI sensor. The AF of the open-ended waveguide with ground plane changes when the size of the ground plane is changes and it is minimum when there is no ground plane. AF of rectangular window sensor is higher and the variation with respect to the frequency is also much more then the open-ended waveguide. FDTD computed AF of rectangular window sensor is agreed with the measurements then the MoM \cite{A_Bhattacharya_rec_wg_emi_sensors}. AF of horn antenna is low and variation with respect to the frequency is less for a efficient EMI sensor. Dielectric field horn or dielectric cone loaded horn improves the gain of the horn and according to the Eqn.~(4) of \cite{Seo_Cho_disk_loaded_cylindrical_dipole_EMC}, AF will decrease. But this works shows that the AF of dielectric field horn or dielectric con loaded horn has higher AF then the air field horn of the same size. This forced to conclude that a good radiator is not good sensor at every times. AF of the horn antenna for orthogonal incident field is too much high. In practice the received power is too low to separate itself from the EMI noise present in the environment. This disadvantage of the horn antenna can be removed if circular horn is used. The AF of circular horn is also too much low and the variation of AF also low for good EMI sensor. 

