Being time-domain technique, FDTD directly calculates the impulse response of an electromagnetic system. Therefore, a single FDTD simulation can provide either ultra wide band temporal waveforms or the sinusoidal steady state response at any frequency within the excitation spectrum. In case of FDTD, specifying a new structure to be modelled is reduced to a problem of mesh generation rather than the potentially complex reformulation of an integral equation. %For example, FDTD requires no calculation of structure-dependent Green functions. This technique can easily be extended to determine the CAF of any other types of antennas. 




